## 🔍 SigNoz Observability Integration

### **MANDATORY: Dual Logging System (Terminal + SigNoz)**

The Intelitor system implements a revolutionary dual logging architecture that ensures every log appears in BOTH the developer's terminal AND SigNoz simultaneously. This provides immediate developer feedback while maintaining comprehensive observability.

### **🎯 Dual Logging Architecture**

```elixir
# MANDATORY: Both backends must ALWAYS be active
config :logger,
  backends: [:console, LoggerJSON],  # DUAL LOGGING: Console + JSON
  level: :info

# Console backend for immediate visibility
config :logger, :console,
  format: "$time $metadata[$level] $message\n",
  metadata: [:request_id, :tenant_id, :trace_id, :user_id]

# JSON backend for SigNoz integration
config :logger_json, :backend,
  formatter: LoggerJSON.Formatters.Datadog,
  metadata: :all  # Include all metadata for comprehensive observability
```

### **🚀 SigNoz Setup and Configuration**

```bash
# 1. Start SigNoz using Podman-Compose (container-only - MANDATORY)
git clone -b main https://github.com/SigNoz/signoz.git
cd signoz/deploy/
# ✅ MANDATORY: Use ONLY podman-compose (Docker is BANNED)
podman-compose -f docker/clickhouse-setup/docker-compose.yaml up -d

# 2. Configure Intelitor for SigNoz
export OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT="http://localhost:4317"
export SIGNOZ_ACCESS_TOKEN="your-access-token"
export SIGNOZ_DASHBOARD_URL="http://localhost:3301"

# 3. Verify dual logging is working
podman exec intelitor-app iex -S mix
# In IEx:
Logger.info("TEST: Dual logging verification", test_id: 123)
# You should see this in BOTH terminal AND SigNoz UI
```

