  Key benefits:

  - Edit anywhere: Use your favorite IDE/editor on the host
  - Run anywhere: Code executes in the container environment
  - Instant sync: Changes appear immediately in both directions
  - No manual copying: No need for docker cp or rebuild commands

  Example workflow:

  1. Developer edits file in VSCode on host: lib/my_module.ex
  2. File instantly appears in container at: /workspace/lib/my_module.ex
  3. Phoenix detects change and recompiles
  4. Browser refreshes with new code

  2. Automatic Code Reloading: Phoenix LiveView and templates update seamlessly

  What it provides:

  Phoenix's built-in code reloading works inside the container just like it would on the host, including:
  - Elixir module recompilation
  - LiveView component updates
  - Template (HEEx) changes
  - CSS/JS asset updates

  How it works:

  # In config/dev.exs - Phoenix watchers configured for container paths
  config :intelitor, IntelitorWeb.Endpoint,
    live_reload: [
      patterns: [
        ~r"priv/static/.*(js|css|png|jpeg|jpg|gif|svg)$",
        ~r"lib/intelitor_web/(live|views|components)/.*(ex|heex)$"
      ]
    ]

  # Container-aware file watching
  config :intelitor, IntelitorWeb.Endpoint,
    watchers: [
      esbuild: {Esbuild, :install_and_run, [:default, ~w(--sourcemap=inline --watch)]},
      tailwind: {Tailwind, :install_and_run, [:default, ~w(--watch)]}
    ]

  Key benefits:

  - No container restart needed: Code changes apply without rebuilding
  - LiveView state preserved: Component state maintained during reloads
  - Instant feedback: See changes in <100ms
  - Full dev experience: All Phoenix dev features work in containers

  Example:

  # You change a LiveView component
  defmodule IntelitorWeb.DashboardLive do
