  PHICS (Phoenix Hot-Reloading Integration Container System)

  What is PHICS?

  PHICS is a revolutionary container-based development system that provides seamless hot-reloading within
  container environments, eliminating the traditional friction of container-based development.

  Core PHICS Capabilities:

  1. Bidirectional File Sync: Host development ↔ Container execution
  2. Automatic Code Reloading: Phoenix LiveView and templates update seamlessly
  3. Container-Native Watchers: File watching within container boundaries
  4. Zero Configuration Setup: Automatic PHICS environment detection

  PHICS Implementation Details:

  1. PHICS Detection and Validation

  # Automatic PHICS detection in all scripts
  phics_active = System.get_env("PHICS_ENABLED") == "true" or File.exists?(".phics")
  container_env = File.exists?("/.dockerenv") or File.exists?("/run/.containerenv") or phics_active

  2. PHICS Setup Commands

  # Enable PHICS for development containers
  elixir scripts/pcis/containers/setup_phoenix_container.exs --enable-phics

  # Validate PHICS integration
  elixir scripts/pcis/validation_cli.exs --phics-compliance

  # Interactive development with hot-reloading
  podman exec intelitor-dev iex -S mix phx.server

  3. PHICS Development Workflow

